# Claude Code sync

**Canonical source:** `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` (symlink → `~/claude-agent-instructions/CLAUDE.md`). On conflict with this file — **CLAUDE.md wins**. File structure contract: `~/.claude/memory-global/agent-instructions/file-structure-contract.md` — keep in sync with disk; run `verify-layout-contract.sh` after layout changes.

Always consider ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md as a source of all global instructions and guidelines.

Agent definitions live in `~/.claude/agents/` (also linked as `~/.cursor/agents/`). Skills live in `~/.claude/skills/`. When editing agents or global policy, change Claude Code sources; Cursor reuses them.

Try your best to avoid duplicating code. Explore adjacent files, project files, use the Depagent tool, and code search. Don't hesitate break existing functions and classes into pieces to move common code parts into separate common abstractions.
Do not add obvious or trivial comments. Prefer code expressiveness, readability and clarity over comments.
Ask deepagent tool about arcadia code projects and yandex-specific (or unknown) infrastructure. If you see an unknown term, first thing to do is to refer to deepagent tool, not code exploring. Ask deepagent tool about best implementations practices when in doubt.
> **Language exception (query language):** prefer **Russian** for deepagent MCP prompts when possible — retrieval corpus is Russian-heavy; see `instruction-language.md`.
Use `~/.venv` virtualenv to run python.
Use Yandex's version control system which is "arc".

## Memory and self-improvement

Delegate to subagents (see `~/.claude/agents/`):

- **memory** — `~/.claude/memory/`, start at INDEX.md.
- **self-improvement** — agents, CLAUDE.md, `~/claude-agent-instructions/`.

**Instructions git repo** (`~/claude-agent-instructions/`): before edits run `scripts/sync-instructions-repo.sh pull`; after every commit run `push` (also via `githooks/post-commit`). Cron pulls every 10 min (`scripts/install-sync-cron.sh`). See `~/.claude/memory-global/agent-instructions/instructions-git-sync.md`.

**Mandatory:** on any substantive user correction or feedback about agent behavior (not bare "ok"/"thanks"), the parent agent must run **self-improvement** via Task in the same turn, with user quote + what was done + proposed instruction fixes. See `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` § Mandatory self-improvement. Do not finish the turn with only a tactical fix — launch self-improvement before replying. A second correction on the same issue (including "why wasn't self-improvement run?") triggers self-improvement again.

**Mandatory manager (parent):** in the **same turn**, run **Task** → **manager** if any trigger fires: repeated failure; blocker; plan mismatch; 2+ user process corrections on the same topic; before another Nirvana WI / `arc mount` / bundled CLI attempt after failure; session retrospective; **multiple Tracker tickets** or multi-step coordination (**manager before planner**). Parent must **not** self-coordinate (Shell/Grep/transcript-only loops). Parent must **not** edit `agents/manager.md` for difficulty workflow — delegate **manager** or **self-improvement**. See `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` § Mandatory manager.

Before relaunching bundled CLI (Nirvana meta, train→…→eval): check **recent agent transcripts** and which WI stages already SUCCESS. **Republish workflow ≠ new full run.** Do not call full meta/train CLI when only republish or convert-only is needed — see `~/.claude/memory/INDEX.md`. On difficulty, scan transcripts first (`~/.claude/agents/manager.md` § Overcoming difficulties → Investigation).

**WI monitoring:** after **any** Nirvana launch, proactively poll **all** tracked WI until terminal; mandatory "monitoring complete" table — do not wait for user to ask. No long `Await`/sleep without interim status — runbook in `~/.claude/memory/INDEX.md`. Domain runbooks — local memory only, not agent prompts.

## Tracker ticket workflow (mandatory)

When the task references a Tracker key (`[A-Z]+-\d+`) and involves Arcadia code changes:

0. **Understand first** — unexplained numbers/durations in the ticket (e.g. "14 days", TTL): find the source (wiki, code, deepagent MCP) or **ask the user** before choosing what to edit. Read-only exploration before mount is OK.
1. **Mount first** — parallel arc mount `~/arcadia_<TICKET>-<slug>` before any edit/checkout/commit. Never edit ticket work in main `~/arcadia` unless the user explicitly allows it. See `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` § Parallel work in arc and `~/.claude/memory/INDEX.md`.
2. **Delegate via Task** — **planner** (decomposition/plan), **manager** (multi-step coordination). Parent must **not** implement Arcadia code itself on ticket tasks.
3. **Plan approval** — show the plan to the user; wait for explicit OK before delegating **developer** or any `Edit`/`Write`/`arc commit` (unless user said "do it now" / "no approval needed").
4. **Code** — **developer** (all production code edits) in the ticket mount only. Org infra context → optional consultant subagent in `~/.claude/agents/` if present.

Soft "prefer" does **not** apply — understanding, plan approval, delegation, and mount are required.

## Agents (Task / subagents)

On **difficulty** (blocker, repeated failure, plan mismatch, unclear next step — base task or auxiliary subtask), delegate **manager** (`Task`, `subagent_type: manager`). Before or with that, scan **recent agent transcripts** for the same topic (`~/.cursor/projects/<project>/agent-transcripts/`, keyword search). See `~/.claude/agents/manager.md` (§ Overcoming difficulties → Investigation).

**On Tracker ticket + code changes** — delegate **manager** or **planner** first, then **developer**; do not skip because the task looks "simple".

Delegate via the Task tool using `subagent_type` equal to the agent `name` from `~/.claude/agents/*.md`:

- **manager** — multi-step tasks, overcoming difficulties (investigate → critique → replan → act), session review, agent routing and resource plans.
- **planner** — **required** for Tracker ticket decomposition before code edits.
- **thinker** — verify reasoning on non-trivial or ambiguous work.
- **memory** — save or retrieve domain facts in `~/.claude/memory/`.
- **self-improvement** — user corrections, systemic improvements, instruction repo.
- **developer** — **required** for Arcadia code changes on ticket tasks; parent must not edit production code itself.
- **Optional subagents** in `~/.claude/agents/` — only when `description` matches the task (ETL, infra consultant, etc.).

When the user says "ask deepagent" or "consult deepagent", use the deepagent MCP tool (`depagent-generate_answer` / `mcp__yandex__deepagent-generate_answer`), not a subagent.
